Rating: 4
As I am pregnant, I was craving vegetarian borscht all day long today. After consulting this recipe and a russian cooking website, I made this version with a couple of changes. First of all, I omitted the canned broth. Next, I took half the beets and cut them into thin strips. I poured cold water over them and let them boil at a slow roll for about 10-15 minutes, or until they lose their color. This gives the borscht a brighter color, as well as eliminating the need for the broth by intensifying the flavor. Meanwhile, I shredded the rest of the beets and all the other veggies + carrots (i don't know why the recipe is missing this vital ingredient). I added the potatoes and cabbage to the boiling pot. At the same time I sauteed the onions and carrots in a heavy skillet. Then I added the rest of the shredded beets, and once they were soft, added a tbsp of tomato paste and a bit of the cooking liquid from the pot and let it infuse for about 10 more minutes. After that was done, I added the mixture to the soup pot and let it boil for another 5 minutes, or until the cabbage and potatoes were tender. Then it was time for the dill. And the results were fantastic! My craving was satisfied (at least for the evening) and the best part is that I will have delicious leftovers for at least a couple of more days. Borscht is always better the next day :)

